OL,3,CPlymouth set for referendum over
OL,4,Cwhether to have a 'directly elected
OL,5,Cmayor'
OL,7,FPlymouth residents will vote in a
OL,8,Freferendum over whether to install a
OL,9,F'directly elected mayor'.
OL,11,FA petition has been handed to the city
OL,12,Fcouncil, automatically triggering a
OL,13,Fpublic vote, which must be held within
OL,14,Fsix months.
OL,16,FUnder the current system, the council
OL,17,Fleader is elected by councillors. This
OL,18,Fcould be replaced by an elected mayor,
OL,19,Fwith broadly the same powers.
